wiki.text:
*High Redundancy Actuation (HRA), a new approach to fault tolerant control in
the area of mechanical actuation. *Variable valve actuation, any mechanism or
method that can alter the shape or timing of a valve lift event within an
internal combustion engine. *Actuation, a type of self-realization referred to
in Aristotle's philosophy of entelechy.
